byline.contributor: The New York Times contributed reporting.

abstract: Michael Brown, songwriter and keyboardist for band Left Banke, dies at age 65.
lead_paragraph: Mr. Brown was a writer of “Walk Away Renee,” the band’s biggest hit and one of Rolling Stone’s 500 greatest songs of all time.

headline.main: Michael Brown, Songwriter and Keyboardist for the Left Banke, Dies at 65
headline.print_headline: Michael Brown, 65, Keyboardist for the Left Banke

snippet: Mr. Brown was a writer of “Walk Away Renee,” the band’s biggest hit and one of Rolling Stone’s 500 greatest songs of all time.
